TITLE: Fox News's Gianno Caldwell shares tragic news of his teenage brother's murder in Chicago
SUMMARY: On Saturday, Fox News analyst Gianno Caldwell shared the tragic news that his teenage brother was shot and killed in Chicago on Friday, amid a crime wave in the city.

TITLE: Biden signs gun control bill in wake of deadly mass shootings: 'Lives will be saved'
SUMMARY: President Biden signed the larget gun control bill in 30 years into law Saturday after it passed through Congress with bipartisan support.

TITLE: What's next for a Supreme Court ever-more divided
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court overturned Roe v Wade after 50 years. Justice Samuel Alito emphasizes that the decision does not open the door to question other precedents outside of abortion.

TITLE: Supreme Court abortion ruling: Citizens predict how historic decision might impact midterm elections
SUMMARY: Demonstrators who gathered outside the Supreme Court following the ruling that overturned Roe v. Wade shared thoughts on the impact the decision might have on midterm elections.

TITLE: Monkeypox mutating more than previously thought, researchers say
SUMMARY: The monkeypox outbreak has spread to 25 U.S. states and the District of Columbia. Portugal scientists warn about the possible "accelerated evolution" of the virus.

TITLE: Illinois primary: Trump's Republican clout again on the line as Reps. Davis, Miller face off
SUMMARY: Donald Trump headlines a rally Saturday for Rep. Mary Miller ahead of Tuesday's GOP primary, when she faces off with fellow Republican Rep. Rodney Davis in the newly drawn 15th District

TITLE: What is mifepristone? Abortion medication in focus after Supreme Court Roe v. Wade decision
SUMMARY: Mifepristone pills are used with misoprostol to end an early pregnancy. The drug blocks a hormone called progesterone, according to the Food and Drug Administration.

TITLE: Mississippi Gov. Tate Reeves 'ecstatic' over Supreme Court abortion ruling, says it's a 'win for life'
SUMMARY: Mississippi Gov. Tate Reeves has reacted to the Supreme Court's decision to overturn Roe v. Wade, saying he is “ecstatic” about the move he hailed as a “win for life."

TITLE: Supreme Court ruling: Fmr Planned Parenthood director argues Left's extreme stance on abortion sparked ruling
SUMMARY: Former Planned Parenthood director Abby Johnson claims the Left is responsible for the decision to overturn Roe v. Wade due to 'extremist position' on abortion.

TITLE: Andrew Gillum, defeated Florida candidate and ex-CNN analyst, was media darling before swift fall from grace
SUMMARY: Former media darling Andrew Gillum was portrayed as an authentic, promising young voice in the Democratic Party until a series of scandals and criminal charges.

TITLE: Supreme Court's Roe ruling requires a Christian response to abortion that must offer hope, not judgment
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court's decision to overturn Roe v Wade is something many Christians have long hoped would happen. So what should these Christians do now?

TITLE: Why Supreme Court abortion decision empowers women
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade and our national perspective on motherhood is being remade.

TITLE: Billie Eilish and Phoebe Bridgers condemn SCOTUS ruling at Glastonbury
SUMMARY: Billie Eilish and Phoebe Bridgers expressed their emotions on the Supreme Court ruling overturning Roe v. Wade during their individual Glastonbury Festival performances in England.

TITLE: Protests erupt across US after Supreme Court reverses Roe v. Wade
SUMMARY: Pro-choice and pro-life activists took to the streets in U.S. cities to allow their voices to be heard after the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade.

TITLE: Norway nightclub shooting: 2 dead, 10 injured in suspected terror-linked attack
SUMMARY: A mass shooting at a Norway nightclub and the surrounding area that left two dead and 10 injured is being investigated as a suspected terrorist-linked attack. It happened during Oslo's Pride festival.

TITLE: Arizona abortion protest: Police release tear gas, lawmakers ‘held hostage’ in Senate building
SUMMARY: The U.S. Supreme Court's overturning of Roe v. Wade has sparked a protest in Phoenix, Arizona, where protesters attempted to breach the state Senate building and created a dangerous situation for lawmakers.

TITLE: Cori Bush speaks at pro-choice rally where protesters call abortion 'act of love,' demand no restrictions
SUMMARY: Pro-choice protesters in St. Louis, Missouri demanded no restrictions on abortion after the U.S. Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade on Friday.

TITLE: Far-left radicals find targets using UGA professors' map of pro-life clinic addresses
SUMMARY: The Crisis Pregnancy Center Map provides a list of addresses of pro-life pregnancy centers, which have been targeted in a wave of violence.

TITLE: Youngkin supports banning abortions in Virginia after 15 weeks following SCOTUS overturning Roe v. Wade
SUMMARY: Virginia Gov. Glenn Youngkin lauded the Supreme Court's decision to overturn Roe v. Wade and said he wants a 15-week abortion ban in the commonwealth.

TITLE: Bill Maher: Trump could win 2024 'so easy' if he'd 'just let go' of 2020
SUMMARY: "Real Time" host Bill Maher argued that Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis is a stronger candidate in 2024 than Donald Trump, who he said could win easily if he'd "let go" of 2020.
